WEBVTT

00:02.043 --> 00:05.463
MURPHY:
You have to help me get Jess.

00:05.505 --> 00:07.507
Did you hear me?
I need your help.

00:10.802 --> 00:12.679
Why on earth would
I ever help you?

00:12.721 --> 00:14.597
Hey, you're still here?

00:14.639 --> 00:16.474
(whispers):
It's Murphy.

00:16.516 --> 00:18.143
I'm ready to turn myself in.

00:18.184 --> 00:20.603
Uh-huh. And
what do you want?

00:20.645 --> 00:24.024
Jess. She was kidnapped,
and I need you to get her out.

00:24.065 --> 00:25.442
Who kidnapped her?

00:25.483 --> 00:26.818
This guy named Josiah.

00:26.860 --> 00:28.111
He took over Nia's business.

00:28.153 --> 00:29.821
Arrest him, too. I don't care.

00:29.863 --> 00:31.656
Just get her out.

00:31.698 --> 00:33.033
(whispering):
The drugs.

00:33.074 --> 00:35.243
That must be where
the cartel shipment went.

00:35.285 --> 00:37.662
We need to get the entire stash
to get the chief on board.

00:37.704 --> 00:39.205
Josh.

00:39.247 --> 00:40.623
Say something.

00:40.665 --> 00:42.125
Trust me, this isn't
gonna happen without it.

00:42.167 --> 00:43.460
I'm sorry. Just--
I need your help.

00:43.501 --> 00:45.128
Fine. Fine.

00:45.170 --> 00:46.629
We'll get Jess.

00:46.671 --> 00:48.089
But we'll also need the heroin.

00:48.131 --> 00:50.508
Every brick.

00:54.554 --> 00:57.182
Does Josiah keep the
drugs at the arcade?

01:00.727 --> 01:02.228
Yeah.

01:04.689 --> 01:06.399
You can have it.

01:06.441 --> 01:09.110
All of it is at Downtown Empire
Arcade on 35th Street.

01:09.152 --> 01:10.195
That's where Jess is, too.

01:10.236 --> 01:12.822
One more thing.
What?

01:12.864 --> 01:15.575
Look, we both know
that you didn't kill Nia alone.

01:15.617 --> 01:18.787
So I also want Felix Bell,
Max Parish

01:18.828 --> 01:20.622
and Jessica Damon.
(tutting) Josh.

01:20.663 --> 01:22.123
I'm the one you want.

01:22.165 --> 01:24.125
I am. Leave them out of it.

01:24.167 --> 01:25.752
I know how much
your friends mean to you.

01:25.794 --> 01:26.753
So...

01:26.795 --> 01:28.755
all four of you.

01:28.797 --> 01:29.881
Deal?

01:33.176 --> 01:34.552
(whispering):
What...

01:34.594 --> 01:35.637
what is it?

01:35.678 --> 01:37.055
What's
he saying?

01:37.097 --> 01:38.473
I heard him
say my name.

01:38.515 --> 01:40.558
(exhales, sniffles)

01:40.600 --> 01:42.852
He wants you and... Max

01:42.894 --> 01:44.437
and Jess, too.

01:45.730 --> 01:46.689
(grunts softly)

01:46.731 --> 01:48.650
(sighs)

01:49.567 --> 01:51.903
Felix.
(sniffles)

01:53.571 --> 01:55.323
Fine.

01:59.285 --> 02:00.370
Deal.

02:01.871 --> 02:03.665
I'll text you my number.

02:03.706 --> 02:06.626
Okay. Give me till the morning
to secure you a safe house.

02:06.668 --> 02:08.336
I'll send the details.

02:08.378 --> 02:10.380
Josiah only gave us
until 9:00 p.m. tomorrow night.

02:10.421 --> 02:11.881
Well, as long as you surrender
before then,

02:11.923 --> 02:13.508
that won't be a problem.

02:15.468 --> 02:16.553
Okay.

02:17.512 --> 02:20.140
See you tomorrow, Murphy.

02:20.181 --> 02:21.808
(phone slams in cradle)

02:22.809 --> 02:24.310
(exhales)

02:27.605 --> 02:29.524
(sighs)

02:29.566 --> 02:32.527
Now all we got to do is
convince Max. (exhales)

02:36.406 --> 02:38.491
♪ ♪

02:44.414 --> 02:45.999
(door closes)

02:46.040 --> 02:48.126
(distant chatter,
video game sounds)

03:10.982 --> 03:13.860
It's not poisonous or anything.

03:15.445 --> 03:17.071
(soft crunching)

03:17.113 --> 03:18.406
See?

03:20.366 --> 03:21.451
Come on.

03:21.492 --> 03:23.620
You haven't eaten anything.

03:31.669 --> 03:33.338
I'm Alex.

03:34.631 --> 03:37.592
Look, I know
what you must think.

03:37.634 --> 03:39.969
What kind of person works
for someone like Josiah?

03:41.429 --> 03:43.223
For what it's worth,

03:43.264 --> 03:44.599
I'm...

03:44.641 --> 03:46.976
I'm taking care
of my little sister.

03:49.354 --> 03:51.147
What Josiah's
doing to you,

03:51.189 --> 03:54.108
it's not okay.

04:03.910 --> 04:05.995
(soft crunching)

04:07.455 --> 04:08.581
(weakly):
It's really good.

04:08.623 --> 04:11.209
Peanut butter, jelly and chips.

04:11.251 --> 04:12.710
It's my sister's favorite.

04:14.587 --> 04:17.257
I heard
you were a vet.

04:17.298 --> 04:18.925
What?

04:18.967 --> 04:21.052
Oh, um...

04:22.845 --> 04:24.847
Yeah, I...

04:25.932 --> 04:28.101
I was. I...

04:29.352 --> 04:31.729
I-I am. I don't know.

04:31.771 --> 04:33.690
Why'd you get into this?

04:33.731 --> 04:35.817
♪ ♪

04:37.151 --> 04:38.111
Oh.

04:38.152 --> 04:39.779
I, uh...
(sniffles)

04:39.821 --> 04:42.282
Hey, hey, hey.

04:42.323 --> 04:43.408
It's okay.

04:44.367 --> 04:46.995
It's gonna be okay.

04:48.579 --> 04:50.415
Is there anything I can get you?

04:53.293 --> 04:54.502
(sniffles)

04:54.544 --> 04:57.255
I know that this
sounds stupid,

04:57.297 --> 04:59.674
given the
circumstances, but...

04:59.716 --> 05:02.510
(sighs)
I usually have, like...

05:02.552 --> 05:03.803
three cups of coffee a day,

05:03.845 --> 05:05.805
and my head is pounding, so...

05:05.847 --> 05:07.724
can...

05:07.765 --> 05:09.475
can you find me some caffeine?

05:09.517 --> 05:11.936
Sure thing.

05:13.855 --> 05:15.815
Alex?

05:15.857 --> 05:18.192
Thank you.

05:23.281 --> 05:26.326
(door closes, lock clicks)

05:26.367 --> 05:28.369
DARNELL:
Max's phone
still isn't going through.

05:28.411 --> 05:30.496
Okay, how's the stupid list
coming?

05:30.538 --> 05:31.748
Can you-- can you hurry up?

05:31.789 --> 05:33.124
It takes more than
one minute to find

05:33.166 --> 05:34.834
every restaurant
in Winnipeg

05:34.876 --> 05:37.587
that could be considered
a diner, okay?

05:37.628 --> 05:38.796
I can't believe you didn't
get the name of it.

05:38.838 --> 05:40.381
Well, it's not exactly like

05:40.423 --> 05:42.050
Max and I were chatting it up

05:42.091 --> 05:45.720
before we all left...
for obvious reasons.

05:45.762 --> 05:48.056
What obvious reasons?

05:48.097 --> 05:50.975
You know.

05:51.017 --> 05:52.268
The motel.
(scoffs)

05:52.310 --> 05:54.145
Can you stop talking about that?

05:54.187 --> 05:56.147
Please.

05:58.107 --> 05:59.525
List is done.

06:01.152 --> 06:02.612
Here, why don't you guys
take these.

06:02.653 --> 06:04.947
I'll use the phone
in our room for the rest.

06:04.989 --> 06:06.449
We're supposed to be
asking for a Kyle Green?

06:06.491 --> 06:07.784
FELIX:
I would try Max Parish, too.

06:07.825 --> 06:09.285
I have no idea what name
he could be using.

06:09.327 --> 06:10.828
There isn't anything
at the arcade that can

06:10.870 --> 06:12.288
tie you guys
to Josiah, right?

06:12.330 --> 06:14.540
He said he wants
every brick,

06:14.582 --> 06:16.376
and I don't want you going
down because of us.

06:20.254 --> 06:22.423
No, we're good.

06:22.465 --> 06:24.133
Okay.

06:25.927 --> 06:26.886
Come on, Pretzel.

06:26.928 --> 06:28.721
Find outside.

06:28.763 --> 06:30.765
FELIX:
I'll let you guys know
if we find anything.

06:36.479 --> 06:38.606
(door shuts)

06:38.648 --> 06:40.608
You okay?

06:42.819 --> 06:44.195
Look, Josiah's not gonna know

06:44.237 --> 06:45.947
you were in on this.

06:48.282 --> 06:51.786
But are we really gonna be
working with Five-O now?

06:51.828 --> 06:54.080
Come on, man.
We're not.

06:54.122 --> 06:58.209
We are not. All we're doing
is keeping our mouths shut.

07:00.378 --> 07:02.630
And it doesn't bother you that
all that "H" is gonna end up

07:02.672 --> 07:04.173
in some evidence locker
somewhere?

07:04.215 --> 07:06.801
No.

07:12.890 --> 07:14.267
Okay.

07:14.308 --> 07:17.186
Yeah, I'm looking
for a Kyle Green.

07:17.228 --> 07:19.522
Yeah, he would've
just started.

07:21.941 --> 07:23.901
JOSH:
Where's the chief?
He's late.

07:23.943 --> 07:25.653
GENE:
Don't worry, he'll be here.

07:25.695 --> 07:27.738
But remember, let's not
mention Murphy.

07:27.780 --> 07:29.949
All right? We're just gonna
keep this about the drugs.

07:29.991 --> 07:32.994
That is all the chief
cares about.

07:33.035 --> 07:35.288
Hey, Chief, thank you
for coming in so late.

07:35.329 --> 07:37.331
It's not a problem, as long
as you've actually found

07:37.373 --> 07:38.958
the rest of that
cartel shipment.

07:39.000 --> 07:41.002
Yeah, we have. We're just
waiting approval on the raid.

07:41.043 --> 07:44.297
Well, I'll call SWAT Monday and
we'll put something together.

07:44.338 --> 07:46.716
With all due respect, sir,
time is of the essence here.

07:46.757 --> 07:48.176
I want to make sure
they don't move anything.

07:48.217 --> 07:49.594
They're not gonna move it
as long as

07:49.635 --> 07:51.095
they don't know we're coming.

07:51.137 --> 07:52.805
Which could happen,
given recent events.

07:52.847 --> 07:54.682
What if we have another mole?
Clemens...

07:54.724 --> 07:57.643
we've been trying to
get this shipment for months.

07:57.685 --> 08:00.521
I'm not gonna blow it
on some ill-prepared raid.

08:00.563 --> 08:02.190
You understand?
Okay, listen...

08:02.231 --> 08:03.858
There's a girl being held
hostage in the basement

08:03.900 --> 08:05.526
with the drugs.

08:05.568 --> 08:07.403
She's gonna die if we don't
get there immediately.

08:07.445 --> 08:08.404
KEITH:
Held hostage?

08:08.446 --> 08:09.655
Come on, give me a break.

08:09.697 --> 08:11.657
What is this, a Die Hard movie?

08:11.699 --> 08:13.326
No, sir, just listen...
Look, Murphy Mason
and her friends

08:13.367 --> 08:15.828
are gonna turn themselves in
if we get Jess Damon out.

08:15.870 --> 08:17.497
We get the drugs, we get
Nia Bailey's killers.

08:17.538 --> 08:19.165
All in one fell swoop.

08:19.207 --> 08:20.750
But we have to act quickly.

08:20.791 --> 08:23.044
So, wait. This is all
the evidence you have?

08:23.085 --> 08:25.671
Yeah, there's enough there.
There isn't.

08:25.713 --> 08:26.881
No way a judge is gonna
issue a search warrant

08:26.923 --> 08:29.300
without significant
probable cause.

08:29.342 --> 08:31.135
It's a dead end.
Sir, please.

08:31.177 --> 08:32.136
Boys...

08:32.178 --> 08:35.640
I'm sorry, it's a no.

08:49.362 --> 08:51.113
Josh blew it when
he mentioned Murphy.

08:51.155 --> 08:52.448
Why don't you just tell him
you're after the chief?

08:52.490 --> 08:54.116
'Cause he's obsessed
with Murphy going away

08:54.158 --> 08:55.409
for, like, ever.

08:55.451 --> 08:56.661
He'll never agree
to cutting her a deal.

08:58.204 --> 08:59.330
You don't know unless you ask.

08:59.372 --> 09:01.958
Trust me, I know.

09:03.709 --> 09:04.835
Well, now what, then?

09:06.462 --> 09:08.422
I don't know.

09:10.383 --> 09:11.467
Go ahead.

09:13.427 --> 09:14.387
Go ahead-- go ahead what?

09:14.428 --> 09:15.555
Ask for help. It's why

09:15.596 --> 09:17.181
you dragged me here, isn't it?

09:19.308 --> 09:20.851
Maybe I just wanted
to hang out.

09:20.893 --> 09:22.645
(chuckles)

09:25.898 --> 09:28.693
Okay, fine, fine. Help.

09:28.734 --> 09:31.737
Okay. There are ways to search
a place without a warrant.

09:31.779 --> 09:34.282
That's literally the point
of a warrant.

09:34.323 --> 09:37.201
Well, there's
a couple loopholes.

09:38.703 --> 09:40.121
Loopholes?
Mm-hmm.

09:40.162 --> 09:42.540
I mean, I was in Narcotics
for ten years.

09:42.582 --> 09:44.333
I had to find a way
to get creative.

09:44.375 --> 09:48.379
Like, uh, plain sight.
Hot pursuit.

09:51.841 --> 09:55.803
You're saying stage Murphy
running into the arcade?

09:55.845 --> 09:58.264
If it happens to lead you
right to Jess...

09:58.306 --> 10:00.266
and the drugs...

10:02.602 --> 10:05.646
I don't know.
It sounds sketchy.

10:07.189 --> 10:09.150
Beat him at his own game.

10:12.820 --> 10:13.988
I'm gonna need another drink.

10:14.030 --> 10:16.198
Attaboy.

10:17.867 --> 10:18.826
Excuse me.

10:18.868 --> 10:21.370
(door unlocks)

10:25.583 --> 10:27.960
How's the head?

10:28.002 --> 10:29.962
Still not great.

10:30.004 --> 10:31.964
I found some Advil.
That should help.

10:32.006 --> 10:33.674
Thank you.

10:35.009 --> 10:36.969
Alex?

10:37.011 --> 10:38.929
Yeah?

10:40.514 --> 10:42.475
I can't die in here.

10:42.516 --> 10:45.394
You said it yourself, you
know. This isn't okay.

10:45.436 --> 10:47.188
And I need you

10:47.229 --> 10:49.148
to promise me

10:49.190 --> 10:51.067
that you won't
let that happen.
I don't have any power

10:51.108 --> 10:53.110
around here.
I-I know. I know.

10:55.488 --> 10:57.865
I know.

10:57.907 --> 11:00.159
But, um...

11:04.080 --> 11:07.041
Can you... Can you just...

11:07.083 --> 11:10.461
Can you just try, please?

11:10.503 --> 11:12.171
Please?

11:15.174 --> 11:17.218
Okay.

11:18.177 --> 11:20.554
Okay.
It's late.

11:20.596 --> 11:22.515
Try to sleep.
Okay.

11:22.556 --> 11:24.058
Thank you.

11:28.270 --> 11:29.772
(door opens)

11:35.611 --> 11:37.697
(sighs)

11:45.246 --> 11:47.498
FELIX:
Yeah, his name is Kyle Green.

11:47.540 --> 11:49.333
He has a beard.

11:49.375 --> 11:51.168
Tall.

11:51.210 --> 11:52.712
WOMAN (over phone):
No, sorry.

11:52.753 --> 11:54.046
Max Parish?

11:54.088 --> 11:55.548
There is no one here
by that name.

11:55.589 --> 11:58.092
Okay. Thanks. Bye.

11:59.593 --> 12:01.303
(sighs)

12:02.221 --> 12:04.348
(dialing phone)

12:04.390 --> 12:07.351
(line ringing)

12:07.393 --> 12:09.478
DOUGIE:
Brownsline Café. This is Dougie.

12:09.520 --> 12:12.273
Hi, Dougie. I'm looking
for a person named Kyle Green.

12:12.314 --> 12:13.941
Does he work there?

12:13.983 --> 12:16.235
No. No, there's no Kyle here.

12:16.277 --> 12:18.487
How about Max Parish?

12:18.529 --> 12:22.116
Y-Yeah, no, no, I-I don't think
there's anyone here

12:22.158 --> 12:23.701
by that-that name, either.

12:23.743 --> 12:25.911
Are you sure?

12:25.953 --> 12:28.038
We're friends of his.

12:28.998 --> 12:30.624
Nope. No Max Parish here.

12:30.666 --> 12:32.251
I-I got to go.
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

12:32.293 --> 12:34.044
(dial tone)

12:34.086 --> 12:35.546
Call-call him back.

12:35.588 --> 12:36.839
Yeah, what do you think
I'm doing?

12:37.757 --> 12:39.592
(line ringing)

12:39.633 --> 12:41.635
DOUGIE:
Brownsline Café.
Dougie?

12:41.677 --> 12:43.596
I just need to speak to Max.

12:43.637 --> 12:45.431
Okay? It...
(dial tone)

12:46.515 --> 12:48.017
Okay that's obviously
where Max is.

12:48.058 --> 12:49.602
And he told this Dougie
not to tell anyone,

12:49.643 --> 12:50.978
so we should, we should
just drive to that place.

12:51.020 --> 12:53.314
It's eight hours away.

12:54.440 --> 12:55.941
Do you have another plan?

12:57.276 --> 12:57.985
(sighs)

13:02.364 --> 13:04.158
I can't believe I came
all the way across town

13:04.200 --> 13:05.701
to listen to your
drunken ideas.

13:05.743 --> 13:08.621
(slurs):
It loosens up the old noggin.

13:08.662 --> 13:10.498
(laughs softly)
Mmm.

13:10.539 --> 13:13.751
So, you seriously want
to stage this pursuit?

13:13.793 --> 13:15.753
What other option do we have?

13:15.795 --> 13:18.589
This could be our only shot
at getting Murphy and them.

13:18.631 --> 13:20.508
No way we can
pull this off.

13:20.549 --> 13:22.092
Mm-mm. What?

13:22.134 --> 13:24.553
Have a drink, and I'm-a tell you
how we're gonna do it.

13:25.679 --> 13:27.097
(British accent):
Barkeep!
No, no, no.

13:27.139 --> 13:29.183
Another round, good sir.
No, no, no. Please.

13:29.225 --> 13:31.352
Thank you.
It's fine. It's all right.

13:31.393 --> 13:32.937
(regular voice):
That's what you guys say, right?
Yeah. Something like that.

13:32.978 --> 13:34.480
(British accent):
Thank you.

13:45.407 --> 13:49.411
♪ Jingle bells, jingle bells,
jingle all the way ♪

13:49.453 --> 13:51.413
♪ Oh, what fun
it is to ride... ♪

13:51.455 --> 13:52.873
Table for four?

13:52.915 --> 13:55.125
Um...

13:55.167 --> 13:57.211
We're actually looking
for Max Parish?

13:57.253 --> 13:58.754
I think he just
started working here?

13:58.796 --> 14:00.756
Can you take these to seven?

14:00.798 --> 14:04.885
♪ Oh, what fun it is to ride
in a one-horse open sleigh... ♪

14:04.927 --> 14:06.887
You must be Murphy.

14:06.929 --> 14:09.348
You must be Dougie.

14:09.390 --> 14:10.891
So you do know Max.

14:10.933 --> 14:13.644
♪ Go, laughing all the way... ♪

14:13.686 --> 14:18.065
Yeah. Yeah, we, uh...
we went to high school together.

14:18.107 --> 14:19.733
I'm assuming you guys
are the ones who kept calling?

14:19.775 --> 14:21.360
Yes.

14:21.402 --> 14:22.611
Why did you pretend like
you didn't know who he was?

14:22.653 --> 14:23.946
Why did you stop
answering our calls?

14:23.988 --> 14:26.323
Look, Max seemed
really freaked out, okay?

14:26.365 --> 14:30.035
He, he told me not to tell
anyone he was coming to town.

14:30.077 --> 14:32.246
Look, just tell us where he is.
He really didn't show.

14:32.288 --> 14:34.164
Come on, man.
I swear to God. Okay?

14:34.206 --> 14:35.499
He was supposed
to start on Tuesday,

14:35.541 --> 14:36.959
but he met some chick,

14:37.001 --> 14:38.544
called me from her
house and-and flaked.

14:38.586 --> 14:41.338
Well, listen up, Dougie,
we just drove eight hours.

14:41.380 --> 14:45.009
So obviously we need his
number, like, now. Okay?

14:45.050 --> 14:48.220
♪ I thought I'd take a ride... ♪

14:48.262 --> 14:49.847
MURPHY:
I love Max.

14:49.889 --> 14:52.725
I'm not gonna do anything
to hurt him.

14:52.766 --> 14:54.143
Okay?

14:54.184 --> 14:56.729
Please give us the number.

14:57.646 --> 15:00.816
♪ He got into a drifted bank
and then... ♪

15:00.858 --> 15:01.859
(line ringing)

15:01.901 --> 15:03.068
Can you get off my ass?

15:03.110 --> 15:05.446
Okay, sorry.
Geez-- close.

15:07.531 --> 15:10.451
LARA (over phone):
Hello?

15:10.492 --> 15:13.913
Um. Hi, c-can I talk to Max?

15:13.954 --> 15:16.874
Um...

15:16.916 --> 15:19.585
Hey.

15:19.627 --> 15:21.545
It's for you.

15:27.092 --> 15:29.345
MAX:
Hello?

15:29.386 --> 15:30.888
Don't hang up.

15:39.396 --> 15:41.106
How did you get this number?

15:41.148 --> 15:42.983
MURPHY:
We're at the, uh, that diner

15:43.025 --> 15:44.818
you were supposed to work at.
What? Th-- What, in Winnipeg?

